---
import PageLayout from '../../layouts/PageLayout.astro';

const articleHtml = `<p>QuickBooks Online users who wish to connect HedgeFlows to their QuickBooks account can do so via the <strong>Settings</strong> page as follows:</p>

<h3>1) Locate QuickBooks Integration</h3>
<p>Locate QuickBooks in the <strong>Accounting system integrations</strong> section of our Settings page and click on "Connect":</p>
<p><img src="/assets/images/help/quickbooks/placeholder-step1.png" alt="Locate QuickBooks in Settings — Accounting system integrations" width="1200" height="700" loading="lazy"></p>

<h3>2) Authorise the integration</h3>
<p>You should see the Intuit login pop-up window requesting you to first log in and then authorise HedgeFlows to connect to your QuickBooks account.</p>
<p>If you have more than one company associated with your Intuit login, please make sure you select the correct company to integrate with.</p>
<p><img src="/assets/images/help/quickbooks/placeholder-step2.png" alt="Authorise HedgeFlows connection in QuickBooks" width="1200" height="700" loading="lazy"></p>

<h3>3) Decide which data you want to import</h3>
<p>Once the QuickBooks integration is authorised, you can close the pop-up window and should see Step 1 of our QuickBooks settings setup. Please check that the company name listed matches your choice.</p>
<p>We provide you with the flexibility to decide which information you wish to import into HedgeFlows. If you have outstanding invoices that were created in QuickBooks several months ago, please choose the relevant historical period to load the data:</p>
<p><img src="/assets/images/help/quickbooks/placeholder-step3.png" alt="Choose which data to import from QuickBooks" width="1200" height="700" loading="lazy"></p>

<h3>4) Decide which data to write back to QuickBooks</h3>
<p>We also offer the flexibility to decide what you wish to write back to QuickBooks. If you wish to benefit from the automation that our platform offers for streamlining your payments and reconciliations of foreign bills and invoices, please select the relevant options.</p>
<p><img src="/assets/images/help/quickbooks/placeholder-step4.png" alt="Choose which data to write back to QuickBooks" width="1200" height="700" loading="lazy"></p>

<h3>5) Setting summary</h3>
<p>Once you have confirmed your settings, you are directed to the summary screen.</p>
<p><img src="/assets/images/help/quickbooks/placeholder-step5.png" alt="QuickBooks integration settings summary" width="1200" height="700" loading="lazy"></p>
<p>You can always come back to this screen and change the configuration via our Settings page.</p>

<h3>6) Finding your imported bills and invoices</h3>
<p>You can locate your imported bills and invoices by navigating to the Invoices page:</p>
<p><img src="/assets/images/help/quickbooks/placeholder-step7.png" alt="Imported QuickBooks invoices in HedgeFlows" width="1200" height="700" loading="lazy"></p>`;
---

<PageLayout
  title="QuickBooks integration - how to get started | Help Centre | HedgeFlows"
  description="Step-by-step guide to connecting your QuickBooks Online account with HedgeFlows for automated foreign currency payments and reconciliation."
>
  <section class="py-12 md:py-16">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 sm:px-6">
      <!-- Breadcrumb -->
      <nav class="flex items-center gap-2 text-sm text-text-muted mb-8">
        <a href="/help" class="hover:text-brand-green transition-colors">Help Centre</a>
        <svg class="w-3.5 h-3.5" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="m8.25 4.5 7.5 7.5-7.5 7.5" />
        </svg>
        <a href="/help/#integrations" class="hover:text-brand-green transition-colors">Integrations</a>
      </nav>

      <h1 class="text-[1.75rem] md:text-[2.25rem] font-bold text-text-heading leading-tight mb-8">QuickBooks integration - how to get started</h1>

      <div class="prose prose-lg prose-gray max-w-none
                  [&_h2]:text-2xl [&_h2]:font-bold [&_h2]:text-text-heading [&_h2]:mt-10 [&_h2]:mb-4
                  [&_h3]:text-xl [&_h3]:font-semibold [&_h3]:text-text-heading [&_h3]:mt-8 [&_h3]:mb-3
                  [&_h4]:text-lg [&_h4]:font-semibold [&_h4]:text-text-heading [&_h4]:mt-6 [&_h4]:mb-2
                  [&_p]:text-text-body [&_p]:leading-relaxed [&_p]:mb-4
                  [&_ul]:list-disc [&_ul]:pl-6 [&_ul]:mb-4 [&_ul_li]:text-text-body [&_ul_li]:mb-2
                  [&_ol]:list-decimal [&_ol]:pl-6 [&_ol]:mb-4 [&_ol_li]:text-text-body [&_ol_li]:mb-2
                  [&_a]:text-brand-green [&_a]:underline
                  [&_table]:w-full [&_table]:border-collapse [&_table]:mb-6
                  [&_th]:bg-gray-50 [&_th]:px-4 [&_th]:py-2.5 [&_th]:text-left [&_th]:text-sm [&_th]:font-semibold [&_th]:text-text-heading [&_th]:border [&_th]:border-gray-200
                  [&_td]:px-4 [&_td]:py-2.5 [&_td]:text-sm [&_td]:text-text-body [&_td]:border [&_td]:border-gray-200
                  [&_img]:rounded-xl [&_img]:shadow-sm [&_img]:my-6
                  [&_iframe]:rounded-xl [&_iframe]:my-6 [&_iframe]:w-full [&_iframe]:aspect-video">
        <Fragment set:html={articleHtml} />
      </div>

      <!-- Back link -->
      <div class="mt-12 pt-8 border-t border-gray-200">
        <a href="/help" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-[0.9375rem] text-brand-green font-medium hover:underline">
          <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M10.5 19.5 3 12m0 0 7.5-7.5M3 12h18" />
          </svg>
          Back to Help Centre
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</PageLayout>
